sql:
SELECT SUM(age_group_15_17) AS total_cases_15_17
FROM health_reports
WHERE reporting_week = '2021-W47';

SELECT reporting_week, total_cases
FROM health_reports
ORDER BY reporting_week;

external_knowledge:
High case counts are defined as total cases greater than 1000; 
'South Region' refers to the region with the name 'South Region'; 
'Disease X' is the specific disease of interest.

